Git Help Commands
 git Help
 git help config
 git help Commands

Git Configuration Commands
 git config --global setting value

Configure User and Email
 git config --global user.name "Your Name"
 git config --global user.email "youremail@yourdomain.subdomain"
 git config --global --list

 cat ~/.gitconfig

Creating a Git Repo
 git init <repo-name>

 git status
 git add <File-name> / .
 git commit -m "<your commit msg here>"

 git commit -am "<your commit msg>" # for files being already tracked by git.

 git reset HEAD <file name> # To unstage file / unstaging changes.
 git checkout -- <filename> # Discard changes in working directory.

 git log # Shows commit history in reverse chronological order.
 git help log # to get help on command.

 git log --oneline --graph --decorate --color

 git rm <filename> # To remove a file from git.

 git add -u # if a file is deleted outside git and is to be committed.
